schema:creator: Tait, C.E.
schema:description: This picture was taken in the earlier days of construction and shows the building up of the hydraulic fill beyond the portion which was lined with concrete. On the right in the middle foreground is the tressle used in carrying the hydraulic discharge pipe from one side of the dam to the other. No each side of the dam is built up from one end to the other, continuously.
schema:name: San Fernando Dam of the Los Angeles Aqueduct, Cal.
schema:publisher: UC Davis Library, Archives and Special Collections
